Have you ever tried it? And if it’s something your family make at Christmas - did I do a good job?!😅

🥗Russian Salad - “Ensalada Rusa”🥗

We have a Latvian man in the family and I wanted to make something traditional for him over the Christmas. I gave the Russian Salad a go as he had mentioned it’s something that he eats on Christmas Day. I’m a big fan of potato/egg salad with pickles but I was sceptical of some of the other ingredients in the mix. 

It was actually very tasty, if I was making it again for myself I’d just leave out the peas. Would you try it? 

Ingredients
6 potatoes, peeled
1 carrot, or more to taste
4 whole eggs
6 large pickles, cut into cubes
1 (15 ounce) can peas, drained
½ cup cubed fully cooked ham, or to taste
1 tablespoon chopped fresh parsley, or to taste (Optional)
½ cup mayonnaise

Directions

1. Bring a large pot of water to a boil. Add potatoes and carrot and return to a boil. Add whole eggs and cook until potatoes are tender, 20 to 30 minutes. Drain and slightly cool mixture.

2. Chop potatoes and carrot. Peel and chop eggs.  
3. Mix potatoes, carrot, eggs, pickles, peas, ham, and parsley together in a large bowl; stir in mayonnaise until salad is evenly coated.  
Tips
Dill can be substituted for parsley if desired.

—> Full Itinerary for Doolin, Co. Clare <—

Things to see/do and dining options.

1. Doolin Cave. View the largest Stalactite in Europe. @doolincave 

2. Doolin Ferry Co. Take a trip to the Aran Islands or take in the Stunning views of the Cliff’s of Moher by boat. @doolinferryco 

3. If you visit the Aran islands with Doolin Ferry Co, take a “Capaill and Trap” ride around the island. 

4. Visit Father Ted’s House, officially known as Glanquin Farmhouse, in Lackareagh, County Clare. (Search that in Google maps if you decide to visit). 

5. The Rock Shop, Liscannor 13 mins from Doolin

@therockshopireland is a unique gift shop with a little something for everyone. They have a spacious, bright and airy tea room with beautiful views over Liscannor Bay. #GlutenFree and dairy free cakes available. 

6. Saint Brigid’s Well - St. Brigid’s Well in Liscannor is one of the oldest wells in Ireland rumored to have healing powers. Don’t forget candles and bring an empty bottle so you can take some holy water home. 👼🏼

How to find the well: 
It’s back up the hill from the rock shop (as if you’re heading back to The Cliffs of Moher). You’ll see a spire monument on the left and it’s just across from that at the graveyard. You can park along the road. 

7. The Cliffs of Moher are located on 13 mins from Doolin. It’s an Area of Outstanding Natural Beauty and a different experience every time you visit. 

8. The Burren - It’s a karst landscape of bedrock incorporating a vast cracked pavement of glacial-era limestone, with cliffs and caves, fossils, rock formations and archaeological sites.

Puff Pastry Fruit Braid (and it’s gluten free guys) ⛔️🍞

Puff pastry is extremly easy to work with, you’ll be amazed at the things you can make with little effort. I’m using the gluten free @jus_rol from @supervalu_irl 

For this puff pastry braid recipe, you can use any kind of fruit you’d make a pie/tart with. Also you can use jam, Nutella or cream cheese as your base. I had some Christmas marmalade left over so I used the rest of that and topped with fresh strawberries. 

1. Take the puff pastry out of the fridge and thaw for about 30 min. I use @jus_rol #GlutenFree
2. Using a lined flat baking sheet (I lined wit parchment paper), unfold the puff pastry and lay it flat.
3. Smear mixture (jam, Nutella, cream cheese) on the middle section only. 
4. Place your fruit choice on top of you base mixture. I used strawberries. 
5. Cut 1 inch sections from the center out. Do not slice into the middle section.
6. Start braiding. Start at one end, bring one piece at a time across the center, overlapping and alternating.
7. After you’ve completed your puff pastry braid, use a pastry brush to brush an egg wash over the top and bake!

I baked mine for about 20 mins until it was golden. Allow to cool then serve with fresh cream! 👌🏽

When to start using an eye cream? HOLD to read 📖

In your early 20’s! 👀🤩

SAVE this info for later or tag a 20 year old 👵

The delicate area around your eyes doesn’t produce as much oil as the rest of your skin and therefore ages faster. For that reason, the earlier you start using eye cream, the better. I’m using the Wide Awake Eye Gel from @ellaandjocosmetics 🥰

Once you’ve gone through your usual skincare routine — cleansed, toned, applied serum, and used a moisturiser — take your eye cream and apply it gently with your ring finger. Without tugging, dot the eye cream over your eye area, going up and out towards your temples. Make sure you get the entire eye area. Use eye cream morning and evening for best results.

💆‍♀️Use a pea-sized amount – no need to drown your skin in eye cream.

💆‍♀️Use your ring finger as the delicate eye area requires a delicate touch without too much pressure.

💆‍♀️ Be very gentle while you dab, tap or lightly massage the cream in.

💆‍♀️Work your way out. Apply the eye cream around your orbital bone, starting from the inner corner of your eye, working your way towards the outer corner.

85g Harvest Morn Cornflakes
160g bag Dairyfine Mini Eggs

All available from Aldi 🤗

Method

Break up the chocolate and cut up the butter into small pieces – put them in a medium ovenproof dish.

Melt the mixture over a pan of boiling water.

Once melted, pour in the cornflakes, mix well.

Divide the mixture between paper cases and  use the back of a spoon to push down on the cornflakes and create a nest shape. 

Decorate with the mini eggs and place in the fridge for 2 hours until set.

Meal 3 - 🍔 DIY BIG MAC 🍔

If you’re a coeliac, I’m sure you’ve been longing for a Big Mac since they day of your diagnosis.

Tag a coeliac 🤓 I’ll be sharing meal inspo everyday this week 👍

INGREDIENTS

400g beef mince
2 tbs garlic powder
1 egg
Salt
Pepper
2 Gluten Free Multiseed Thins
½ white onion, finely chopped
¼ head iceberg lettuce, finely shredded
2 slices cheesy singles
2 gherkins, thinly sliced

BIG MAC SAUCE

Ketchup 
Mayonnaise
2 tsp hot dog mustard
1 tbs diced gherkins 
1 tbs diced white onion 
1 tbs vinegar
1 ½ tsp garlic powder
1 tsp paprika

METHOD 

For the Big Mac sauce, combine all the ingredients in a bowl and mix well. Leave the sauce in the fridge until you’re ready to build your Big Mac. 

To make the patties; 

Season the mince with garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Add 1 egg.
Mix well. 
Form into 4 balls. Make the patties as big/small as you like. I made small patties and flattened them down, similar to the original Big Mac. 
Heat oil in a large pan over high heat. Add your patties to the pan turning every few minutes until cooked through. 
Add your cheesy singles on top and allow to melt. 
Lightly toast three Gluten Free Multiseed Thins. 
To build the burgers;

1. Spread a little Big Mac sauce over the bottom base. Top with shredded lettuce and beef patty. 

2. Top with the middle bun layer, and spread with more Big Mac sauce, lettuce, beef patty and gherkins. 

3. Top with burger lid to serve.

SAVE for family friendly museum in Amsterdam 📸✨

The Upside Down Amsterdam is world’s largest upside down social media experience. With 25+ rooms and installations they have a 1500m2 mind-bending and colorful experience for you.

During the experience you can scan your ticket bar code in each room and photos are taken which you can download free of charge. 

Guests are encouraged to take their time in each room. The tour takes about 2hr for a family. You could probably do it in 1.5 hr for couples. 

I’d strongly advise to book your tickets in advance and arrive early if you’re under pressure for time. I booked online before our trip. The queue was out the door and we had to wait about 30 mins before we got in - thats 30 mins after our allocated time slot. So if you have a flight to catch give yourself plenty of time.

This is our third time visiting Cozumel. 🏝️If you’re visiting Playa del Carmen or Cancun I’d highly recommend a day trip over to the island. It’s only 35 minutes by ferry, the water is incredible and there are so many day tour options to choose from 😍 You can book a tour package with a tour operator in your hotel or on 5th Ave (we did that last year when we were here with Phoenix). Alternative you can buy your own ferry tickets and book an excursion on the day. We booked the clear boat tour at the port (on the Playa side - apparently it’s cheaper to book your excursions before you get to Cozumel). The tour operator wanted $120 pp but we managed to get our tickets for $50 pp - if you don’t ask, you don’t get! The tour was 2hrs, short but sweet and our first time on a clear boat which was really cool! 

After the tour we went for lunch in Fuego Restaurant Cozumel - Mexican Tapas Bar & Grill. A bowl of French fries was nearly $10 David was snapping 🤣 the sushi and ceviche was so fresh and delicious it made up for the rip off fries 🍟 

It seems that return ferry’s run every 2hrs. When we checked the return was 2,4,6 and 8pm. I think they fish up at 8pm. That could be subject to change so don’t quote me on that. 

We decided to get the 4pm ferry back to Playa. We had a few drinks across from the port while we waited. It was a completely different experience from last years Cozumel itinerary we love that every experience has been something unexpected. I’d definitely return if we’re here again.

Gluten Free Passion fruit and coconut Hobnob’s cheese cake

Tag a coeliac 😍 I got the recipe from @follainirishpreserves 

Ingredients:

Base: 2 digestives (I used GF hobnobs)  1 tbsp brown sugar light or dark 3 tbsp desiccated coconut ⁠ 3 tbsp finely chopped pecans 2 1⁄2 tbsp melted butter ⁠
 For the mousse: ⁠ 
115g softened cream cheese⁠  150ml Double Cream 200g Folláin Passionfruit Curd⁠

Method: 
1. For the biscuit base:⁠ Preheat oven to 180C. ⁠ Line a sheet pan with baking paper, if desired. ⁠
2. Place biscuits in a bag and seal tightly, using a rolling pin, roll over the bag until finely crushed. - Transfer to a medium-size bowl. ⁠
3. Add the brown sugar, coconut, pecans and melted butter to the bowl with the biscuits and stir well to thoroughly coat the mixture with the butter
4. Transfer the mixture to the prepared pan and bake for 8-10 minutes, or until golden and crunchy, stir halfway through to redistribute.⁠
5. Divide the mixture between 4 jars or ramekins and pack it down slightly with the rounded tip of a spoon. ⁠Allow to cool completely while preparing the mousse.⁠
6. For the mousse: ⁠ Whisk the cream cheese in a medium-size bowl until smooth and lump-free, add the passionfruit curd and whisk together until smooth and creamy. Set aside.⁠
7. With a whisk or a handheld mixer whip the double cream until soft peaks form when you pull up the whisk or mixer.⁠
8. Fold the whipped cream into the Passion Fruit curd mixture until just combined.⁠
9. Divide the mousse between the 4 jars.
10. Garnish:⁠ Passion fruit seeds and Raspberries⁠. Enjoy:⁠ Outdoors, with friends and sunshine…

✨ White Chocolate Salted Caramel Cheesecake ✨

My sister said this was the BEST cheesecake she ever had 👌 I got the recipe from @liliforberg collaboration with @droetkerbakingireland - I will definitely be making it again. It was out of this world 🌍🤤✨

Here’s Lili’s Recipe 👇👇

Serves 12
For the biscuit base
300g digestive biscuits
150g unsalted butter, room temperature or melted

For the cheesecake
800g full-fat cream cheese
150g (1½ cups) icing sugar
1 tsp vanilla extract
60ml (¼ cup) cream
150g white chocolate chips (melted and cooled)

For on top
100g white chocolate chips (melted)
150g salted caramel - I used @follainirishpreserves Caramel with Irish Cream Liqueur 🤤

Method
-Grease a 9 inch/23cm springform tin.
-To make the base, put the biscuits and butter in a food processor and blitz until well combined.
-Put the buttery crumbs into the greased cake tin and press down firmly.
-Place all the ingredients for the cheesecake (except the white chocolate) in a bowl and mix well using a hand mixer.
-add the melted chocolate and whisk until combined. Make sure to leave the melted chocolate out for 10 mins before pouring it out. It needs to be cooled but still liquid.
-Put the cake in the fridge and leave for at least 4 hours, or ideally overnight.
-decorate with salted caramel, melted white chocolate and Dr. Oetker Chocolate Christmas Trees (I had to use stars because I couldn’t find Christmas Trees in stock).

‘TIS THE MULLED WINE SEASON 🍷🐉

Recipe @gimmesomeoven 👌✨

To begin, gather your ingredients. For this mulled wine recipe, you will need:

Wine: The best wine for mulled wine will be fruity and full-bodied, so that it can withstand the heat and not have its flavour completely drowned out by the aromatics. I recommend looking for a bottle of Zinfandel, Merlot, Grenache. 

Brandy: Similar to sangria, it’s also traditional to spike your mulled wine with an extra bit of liqueur. Brandy is the traditional choice, but Cointreau (or another orange liqueur) or tawny port are also delicious alternatives.

Fresh oranges: One of which we will slice and mull in the wine, one of which you can slice and use as a garnish if you’d like. (Edit: To minimize bitterness, I recommend peeling the orange before simmering it in the wine.)

Cinnamon: I love making mulled wine with cinnamon sticks, but you could whisk in some ground cinnamon if that’s what you have on hand.

Mulling spices: These vary in mulled wine from country to country, but whole cloves and star anise are my favorites, plus perhaps a few cardamom pods.

Sweetener: Feel free to add your favorite sweetener to taste. Sugar is classic, but I prefer to naturally sweeten mine with either maple syrup or honey

HOW TO MAKE MULLED WINE:

To make mulled wine, simply…

Combine ingredients. Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and give them a quick stir.

Simmer. Heat until the wine almost reaches a simmer over medium-high heat. (Avoid letting it bubble in any way. Alcohol begins to vaporize at 172°F, so take care to ensure that the wine does not evaporate.) 

Reduce heat to low, cover completely, and let the wine simmer for at least 15 minutes or up to 3 hours.

Strain and season. Using a fine mesh strainer, remove and discard the orange slices, cloves, cinnamon sticks, star anise and ginger. 

Give the mulled wine a taste, and stir in your desired amount of extra sweetener if needed.

Serve. Serve warm in heatproof mugs, topped with your favorite garnishes.

Know before you go! 🤔🗻🧗‍♀️🏔️🌄

The Slieve League cliffs are the highest accessible sea cliffs in Ireland (the title of the highest sea cliffs goes to Croaghaun on Achill) and they’re said to be some of the highest in Europe.

Dublin to Slieve League 🚗⛰️ 3hrs 45 min

Lough Eske Castle to Slieve League 🚙⛰️ 1 hr 

There are two places to park when visiting Slieve League;

1. Lower car park - requires you to make a 45-minute+ moderately strenuous walk to the viewing point. 

2. Upper car park - is right next to the viewing platform. You can drive up through the gates during the off-season, but you need to walk or take the shuttle during peak-season.

The Slieve League car park costs €5 for 3 hours or €15 for the day.

Keep an eye out for the Éire sign. We only noticed it on the walk back down to the car park. 

You’ll find toilets at the visitor centre and at the 1st car park. 

Dress appropriately and wear suitable footwear.
